<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/3795e: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                Queen <persName type="to">Marie</persName> of Roumania</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-06">December
                                    6, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your Majesty’s message<note n="16" xml:id="d325fn16">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_390">p.
                                390</ref>.</note> has given the deepest pleasure, and I beg to
                            assure you that it has been and always will be considered a privilege by
                            the American people and government to do whatever is possible by way of
                            friendly assistance to the people of Roumania.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>